s to invest in stocks of companies operating in the energy sector including companies involved in exploration production and transmission of energy or energy fuels making and servicing of component products for such activities energy research and energy conservation the fund invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations with a focus on largecap and midcap companies it employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis with a bottomup stock picking approach focusing on factors like cash flow and asset valuations in addition to earnings valuations financial prospects the prices of the securities the stock market fundamentals and attractive valuation capitalization volatility expected growth rates and regional exposure and the economy in general to create its portfolio the fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the msci acwi energy index the standard  poors energy sector index the spliced energy index and the global natural resources funds average it employs proprietary research to create its portfolio vanguard specialized funds  vanguard energy fund was formed on may   and is domiciled in the united states detailed description  vanguard boulevardvmalvern pa united statesfounded in  phone  fax  institutionalvanguardcomvgappiipsiteinstitutionalinvestmentsproductoverviewfundid key executives for vanguard specialized funds  vanguard energy fund mr frederick william mcnabb iii chief executive officer and president age  ms kathryn j hyatt treasurer age  mr james a bevilacqua senior vice president partner and equity portfolio manager mr karl edward bandtel portfolio manager age  mr james d troyer cfa portfolio manager compensation as of fiscal year  similar private companies by industry company name region visory llc united states  road partners llc united states t partners llc united states jumpcom inc united states  ontario inc united states recent private companies transactions typedate target no transactions availabl