he nav is calculated by valuing securities at amortized cost which approximates market value change        dividend yieldthe annual rate of return on a share of stock determined by dividing the annual dividend by its current share price in a stock mutual fund this figure represents the average dividend yield of the stocks held by the fund  key fund facts key fund facts expense ratio  as of  lipper peer average expense ratio  as of  designation international large blend inception on  total net assets this represents the total net assets for all share classes of vanguards us funds that share the same investment strategy management and holdings but does not include any collective trusts sharing the same investment mandate  million as of  net assets for vigi   million as of  holdings   as of  management style index benchmark nasdaq intl dividendachieverssel ix dvgitr turnover rate   fiscal yearend   cusip  trading trading iov intraday optimized value tickerintraday optimized value iov also known as the intraday indicative value iiv is the calculated per share price of the etf which is published every  seconds based on the last sale price of each of the underlying securities in the portfolio basket plus any estimated cash amounts associated with the creation unit vigiiv outstanding shares  as of  etf exchange nasdaq stock exchange stylebox stylebox equityinvests in the stocks of companies located in developed and emerging markets excluding the us that have a record of increasing dividends over time central tendency expected range how to read our stylebox   objectivevanguard international dividend appreciation etf seeks to track the performance of a benchmark index that measures the investment return of nonus companies that have a history of increasing dividends investment approachseeks to track the performance of the nasdaq international dividend achievers select index employs a passively managed fullreplication strategythe fund remains fully invested largecap equity emphasizing stocks from developed and emerging markets excluding the united states with a record of growing dividends year over yearlow expenses minimize net tracking error about the benchmark includes an allcap universe of developed and emerging stocks excluding the us that have a history of increasing dividends for at least seven consecutive yearsexcludes stocks that might have low potential for increasing dividendsexcludes reits which generally do not benefit from currently favorable tax rates on qualified dividends total returns as of  view as quarter‑end month‑end as of  view asquarter‑end quarter‑endmonth‑end       ytd  year  year  year since inception  market price    — —  nav    — —  benchmark nasdaq international dividend achievers select index   — — —  focuses on highquality companies located in developed and emerging markets excluding the united states that have both the ability and the commitment to increase their dividends over time the performance data shown represent past performance which is not a guarantee of future results investment returns and principal value will fluctuate so investors shares when sold may be worth more or less than their original cost current performance may be lower or higher than the performance data cited quarterly commentary   total returns details   regional exposure as of   as of    region  vigi benchmark nasdaq international dividend achievers select index  weight europe    pacific    emerging markets    north america   –  middle east    other     total     top  countries as of   as of  country region vigi benchmark nasdaq international dividend achievers select index  weight switzerland europe    canada north america   –  japan pacific    india emerging markets    france europe    china emerging markets    united kingdom europe    australia pacific    netherlands europe    denmark europe    top  equals  of stock country diversification details   sector weightings as of  as of    sector  vigi benchmark nasdaq international 